<subSubSection id="DA9D651A5C13FFBD1FC9F87AFDDA746C" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="576" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="923836915C13FFBD1FC9F87AFDDA746C" blockId="1.[151,1437,1853,2024]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,611]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="576" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C13FFBE1FC9F87AFE9371AF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Remarks.</emphasis>
Generic diagnoses for the adult male of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C13FFBE1C05F87AFC0171AF" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[779,937,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C13FFBE1C05F87AFC0171AF" box="[779,937,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been given by 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C13FFBE1B9BF87AFA9271AE" author="Fittkau, E. J." box="[1173,1338,1926,1953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="1 - 453" refId="ref3508" refString="Fittkau, E. J. (1962) Die Tanypodinae (Diptera: Chironomidae): Die Tribus Anatopyniini, Macropelopiini und Pentaneurini. Abhandlungen zur Larvalsystematik der Insekten, 6, 1 - 453." type="journal article" year="1962">Fittkau (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C13FFBE1A49F87AFF4D71CB" author="Roback, S. S." pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="1 - 410" refId="ref4351" refString="Roback, S. S. (1971) The adults of the subfamily Tanypodinae (= Pelopiinae) in North America (Diptera: Chironomidae). Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 17, 1 - 410." type="journal article" year="1971">Roback (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C13FFBE1FE1F856FDAE71CB" author="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J." box="[239,518,1962,1988]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="353 - 502" refId="ref3784" refString="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J. (1989) 5. The adult males of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region- Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region-Keys and diagnoses. Part 3. Adult males. Entomologica scandinavica, 34 (Supplement), pp. 353 - 502." type="journal article" year="1989">Murray &amp; Fittkau (1989)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C13FFBE1D35F856FC9C71CB" author="Niitsuma, H. &amp; Suzuki, M. &amp; Kawabe, K." box="[571,820,1962,1988]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref3859" refString="Niitsuma, H., Suzuki, M. &amp; Kawabe, K. (2004) Redescriptions of Macropelopia kibunensis and Macropelopia paranebulosa (Diptera, Chironomidae), with biological notes. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 10, 43 - 56." type="journal article" year="2004">
Niitsuma 
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C13FFBE1DA7F857FD4871CB" box="[681,736,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, these diagnoses should be emended to agree with the Patagonian species described here. Recently, 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C13FFBE1DFBF832FC2771E7" box="[757,911,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bethbilbeckia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C13FFBE1DFBF832FC2771E7" box="[757,911,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Bethbilbeckia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C13FFBE1BD2F832FAD271E7" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[1244,1402,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C13FFBE1BD2F832FAD271E7" box="[1244,1402,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1F99FF65FE6676BC" author="Cranston, P. S. &amp; Epler, J. H." box="[151,462,152,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="39 - 136" refId="ref3196" refString="Cranston, P. S. &amp; Epler, J. H. (2013) 5. The larvae of Tanypodinae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic Region-Keys and diagnoses. In: Andersen, T., Cranston, P. S. &amp; Epler, J. H. (Sci. Eds.), The larvae of Chironomidae (Diptera) of the Holarctic Region-Keys and Diagnoses. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 66 (Supplement), pp. 39 - 136." type="journal article" year="2013">Cranston &amp; Epler (2013: 53</bibRefCitation>
, see commentary in 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1DBEFF65FC3176BB" author="Silva, F. L. &amp; Ekrem, T." box="[688,921,153,180]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref4424" refString="Silva, F. L. &amp; Ekrem, T. (2016) Phylogenetic relationships of nonbiting midges in the subfamily Tanypodinae (Diptera: Chironomidae) inferred from morphology. Systematic Entomology, 41, 73 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12141" type="journal article" year="2016">Silva &amp; Ekrem 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1B3BFF65FB7B76BC" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[1077,1235,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1B3BFF65FB7B76BC" box="[1077,1235,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BBC057F85C10FFBD1BD7FF65FABC76BC" box="[1241,1300,153,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is separable from that of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1ECDFF41FDF576D8" box="[451,605,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bethbilbeckia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1ECDFF41FDF576D8" box="[451,605,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Bethbilbeckia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the multiserial temporal setae and the tibial comb on the foreleg. The male of the latter has no tibial comb on the foreleg and uniserial temporal setae (
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1B02FF1DFABD76F4" author="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J." box="[1036,1301,225,251]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="353 - 502" refId="ref3784" refString="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J. (1989) 5. The adult males of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region- Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region-Keys and diagnoses. Part 3. Adult males. Entomologica scandinavica, 34 (Supplement), pp. 353 - 502." type="journal article" year="1989">Murray &amp; Fittkau 1989</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1FBAFEF9FEDD7710" author="Andersen, T." box="[180,373,261,287]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="85 - 90" refId="ref3100" refString="Andersen, T. (2018) Macropelopia (Bethbilbeckia) chilensis n. sp. (Diptera, Chironomidae) from Cajon del Maipo, Chile. Norwegian Journal of Entomology, 65, 85 - 90" type="journal article" year="2018">Andersen (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, however, 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1EFFFEF9FC067710" box="[497,942,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis" subGenus="Bethbilbeckia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1EFFFEF9FD277710" box="[497,655,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1DAEFEF9FC927710" box="[672,826,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Bethbilbeckia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1C42FEF9FC067710" box="[844,942,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses bi- to multiserial temporal setae. Therefore, the foretibial comb may be the only remaining discriminator to separate the male of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1BB3FED5FAF3774C" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[1213,1371,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1BB3FED5FAF3774C" box="[1213,1371,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BBC057F85C10FFBD1A6FFED5FA34774C" box="[1377,1436,297,323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from that of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1E2BFEB1FE177768" box="[293,447,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bethbilbeckia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1E2BFEB1FE177768" box="[293,447,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Bethbilbeckia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The males collected from the Patagonian Andes will not key past couplet 
<quantity id="557F9B745C10FFBD1A06FEB1FAE97768" box="[1288,1345,333,359]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="in" value="13.0">13 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1A46FEB1FEFF7784" author="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="353 - 502" refId="ref3784" refString="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J. (1989) 5. The adult males of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region- Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region-Keys and diagnoses. Part 3. Adult males. Entomologica scandinavica, 34 (Supplement), pp. 353 - 502." type="journal article" year="1989">Murray &amp; Fittkau (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, because the foretibia is armed with an apical row of long bristles instead of small spines (
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1A45FE8DFEA377A0" author="Fittkau, E. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="1 - 453" refId="ref3508" refString="Fittkau, E. J. (1962) Die Tanypodinae (Diptera: Chironomidae): Die Tribus Anatopyniini, Macropelopiini und Pentaneurini. Abhandlungen zur Larvalsystematik der Insekten, 6, 1 - 453." type="journal article" year="1962">Fittkau 1962: 108</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1E17FE69FE7777A0" author="Roback, S. S." box="[281,479,405,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="1 - 410" refId="ref4351" refString="Roback, S. S. (1971) The adults of the subfamily Tanypodinae (= Pelopiinae) in North America (Diptera: Chironomidae). Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 17, 1 - 410." type="journal article" year="1971">Roback 1971: 89</bibRefCitation>
). However, the hypopygial gonostylus resembles those of the many species of 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1A6FFE6AFEAB77DC" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1A6FFE6AFEAB77DC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BBC057F85C10FFBD1E05FE45FEEF77DC" box="[267,327,441,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1EC1FE45FDC177DC" box="[463,617,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bethbilbeckia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1EC1FE45FDC177DC" box="[463,617,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Bethbilbeckia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the broad base and the constricted apical one third (Fittkau &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1A46FE45FF7B77F8" author="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="353 - 502" refId="ref3784" refString="Murray, D. A. &amp; Fittkau, E. J. (1989) 5. The adult males of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region- Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region-Keys and diagnoses. Part 3. Adult males. Entomologica scandinavica, 34 (Supplement), pp. 353 - 502." type="journal article" year="1989">Murray 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In the key to Afrotropical chironomid genera by 
<bibRefCitation id="F6164B605C10FFBD1C03FE21FC4577F8" author="Ekrem, T. &amp; Ashe, P. &amp; Andersen, T. &amp; Stur, E." box="[781,1005,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="813 - 863" refId="ref3342" refString="Ekrem, T., Ashe, P., Andersen, T. &amp; Stur, E. (2017) Chironomidae (non-biting midges). In: Kirk-Springgs, A. H. &amp; Sinclair, B. J. (Eds.), Manual of Afrotropical Diptera. Vol. 2. Nematocerous Diptera and lower Brachycera. Suricata 5. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 813 - 863." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Ekrem 
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1C51FE22FC3977F8" box="[863,913,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1CF7FE22FAFD77F8" authority="Silva &amp; Pinho, 2020" authorityName="Silva &amp; Pinho" authorityYear="2020" box="[1017,1365,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. n." subGenus="Macropelopia">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1CF7FE22FBB077F8" box="[1017,1048,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1B26FE21FB6E77F8" box="[1064,1222,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1BD9FE22FAFD77F8" box="[1239,1365,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1A52FE21FA3577F8" bold="true" box="[1372,1437,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BBC057F85C10FFBD1A52FE21FA3577F8" box="[1372,1437,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
keys to 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1FFEFDFDFE267414" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[240,398,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1FFEFDFDFE267414" box="[240,398,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(couplet 23) if tibial comb is present on fore leg. Therefore, it is considered that the species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="55874D125C10FFBD1E18FDD9FE1C7430" authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[278,436,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="A0F3EA835C10FFBD1E18FDD9FE1C7430" box="[278,436,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BBC057F85C10FFBD1EB3FDD9FE537430" box="[445,507,549,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the apical row of long bristles on the foretibia may be homologous with the foretibial comb consisting of small spines.
</paragraph>
